init_text: When you're 28, science discovers a drug that stops all effects of aging, creating immortality. Your government decides to give the drug to all citizens under 26, but you and the rest of the â€œLost Generations" are deemed too high-risk. When you're 85, the side effects are finally discovered.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: She isn't aging, but the drug has its consequences.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Will you be able to help her?

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You don't think you can protect her from herself or the heinous results of a flawed experiment.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Her fingers and toes have all distorted into claw-like appendages.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: And the worse part is, it's happening right before your eyes.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You need to do whatever it takes to stop the people that did this to her and other innocent victims.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You will be the one to make them pay.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Her pain and discomfort is intensifying each and every day.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: You really can't believe that you just lost the love of your life.
